,"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728",{"_":181,"xml:id":182},"Serena Agodi","SA",{"_":184,"xml:id":185,"ref":186},"Simona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"_":188,"when":189,"who":190},"renumbered files, uris and references","2021-01-19","#SS",{"n":93,"url":94,"height":95,"width":96,"desc":97,"surfaceType":98},[],[194,195,196],"Kaibel, 1890, IG","Korhonen, 2004, IMusCatania","Boeckh, Franz, 1853, CIG",[198,199,200],"Q2SBPG9F","2EUC82DH","TQMVHEVL",[202,203,204,24,29,205,206,207,208,209,207,210,211,118],"isic001308","funerary inscription for kornelios agathemeros",{"_":5},"marble","catina","catania","italy","sicily","museo civico di catania","ancient greek with latin numerals",[],{"title":214,"body":215,"divs":216,"editions":243,"images":253,"handnote":259},"ISic001308. Funerary inscription for Kornelios Agathemeros","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Unknown\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>❦ Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοις) ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span> Κορνήλιος · Ἀγα-\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>θήμερος · ἐζη ·-\u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>σεν ἔτη · XXXVIII \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span> Εὐφροσύνη · ἰδίῳ συ\u003Cspan class=\"small\" title=\"small character: ν\">ν\u003C/span>-\u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>βίῳ μνήμης χάριν \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Unknown\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>❦ΘΚ❦\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΚΟΡΝΗΛΙΟΣΑΓΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΘΗΜΕΡΟΣΕΖΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΣΕΝΕΤΗXXXVIII\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>ΕΥΦΡΟΣΥΝΗΙΔΙΩΣΥ\u003Cspan class=\"small\" title=\"small character: ν\">Ν\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ΒΙΩΜΝΗΜΗΣΧΑΡΙΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001308_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo by students of Liceo M.M. Lazzaro, Catania\" src=\"ISic001308_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001308.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo by students of Liceo M.M. Lazzaro, Catania\" src=\"ISic001308-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text from photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the gods of the underworld. Kornelios Agathemeros lived 38 years. Euphrosyne (set this up) as a memorial for her own partner in life.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">Serena Agodi\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Agli dèi del mondo sotterraneo. Kornelios Agathemeros ha vissuto 38 anni. Eufrosia (lo pose) a ricordo del proprio compagno di vita.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp> This epitaph was found together with ISic001314 (inv. no.272), which was apparently erected by the same man as is commemorated in this text (although it is also possible that they are father and son). The implication is that Euphrosyne was his second wife, who outlived him. The use of Latin numerals in the middle of the Greek text is a clear indication of the co-existence of the two languages in Catania at this date and the ‘interference’ between them (just as the name Cornelius Agathemeros combines Latin and Greek names also).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5695 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">485\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 73 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> Line 1  12-25  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not measured  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[217,220,223,226,229,231,234,237,240],{"id":218,"html":219},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Unknown\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>❦ Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοις) ❦ \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span> Κορνήλιος · Ἀγα-\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan clas